                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">838.51/864: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bailly-Blanchard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-08-28T09:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 28, 1919, 9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s August 20, 6 p.m. Commander Gayler left 25th for Washington via Cuba
                    and Key West with protocol, article 3, section 2 of which should read, after
                    “Haiti” as of December 31, 1916 as acknowledged by the Haitian Government on the
                    12th of April 1919”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
